<ol class="blogroll wp-dark-mode-bg-image">
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-53807" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://blog.apaonline.org/2025/05/09/academic-freedom-including-free-discussion-for-students/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“People often treat ‘freedom of discussion’ as merely another name for freedom of speech. But I think this is a mistake”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Mark Satta on the distinctiveness of freedom of discussion, and academic freedom for students</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-53812" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/10.1177/09567976251331053" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">The doubling-back aversion: “a reluctance to pursue more efficient means to a goal when they entail undoing progress already made”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; distinct from the sunk-cost fallacy (via MR)</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-53799" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://jpandrew.substack.com/p/my-interview-with-galen-strawson" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“I think there’s never been a single good argument for dualism”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; an interview with Galen Strawson</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-53797" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://soundcloud.com/electrophilosophy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">A father-son duo, both philosophers, have released a new album of wild electronic music</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; immerse yourself in the textures &amp; pulses of &#8220;Spin-Oza&#8221; by The Department of Electrophilosophy, aka Marc &amp; Cedric Bobro (fave track so far: &#8220;Sanctuary of Ignorance&#8221;)</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-53784" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://walterveit.substack.com/p/what-is-it-like-to-be-a-crow" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">What is it like to be a crow?</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; a team of philosophers &amp; psychologists look at five dimensions of corvid conscious experience</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-53773" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.truesciphi.ai/p/seeking-a-view-from-nowhere" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“Arguments don’t float in a vacuum. They grow out of the soil they’re planted in”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; one lesson that GPT o3 (a &#8220;reasoning&#8221; LLM) takes from an exercise in which it is asked to respond to a set of thought experiments from different points in philosophy&#8217;s history</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-53766" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.3-16am.co.uk/blog/exclusive-3-16-interview-with-dennis-diderot" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“Other men walk in darkness; the philosopher, who has the same passions, acts only after reflection; he walks through the night, but it is preceded by a torch”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Denis Diderot is &#8220;interviewed&#8221; by Richard Marshall</span></li>
</ol>
<p>Mini-Heap posts usually appear when 7 or so new items accumulate in the <a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://dailynous.com/heap-of-links/">Heap of Links</a>, a collection of items from around the web that may be of interest to philosophers. The Heap of Links consists partly of suggestions from readers; if you find something online that you think would be of interest to the philosophical community, please <a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="mailto:dailynouseditor@gmail.com">send it in</a> for consideration for the Heap. Thank you.<br class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" /><em class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://dailynous.com/2025/05/05/mini-heap-656/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Previous Edition</a> </em></p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/05/12/mini-heap-657/">Mini-Heap</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>